@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title State Machine - database/AutonomousDatabases
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
state "ApplyUpdate" as apply_update
state "SyncSecret" as sync_secret
state "SecretBlocked" as secret_blocked
state "DeletePending" as delete_pending
state "Deleted" as deleted
state "DeleteCleanupBlocked" as delete_cleanup_blocked
[*] --> observe : CreateAutonomousDatabase,\nUpdateAutonomousDatabase
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nAVAILABLE, STANDBY
resolve_by_lookup --> retryable : OCI state in PROVISIONING,\nSTARTING,\nMAINTENANCE_IN_PROGRESS,\nRESTARTING (+6 more)
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in AVAILABLE,\nSTANDBY
observe --> retryable : OCI state in PROVISIONING,\nSTARTING,\nMAINTENANCE_IN_PROGRESS,\nRESTARTING (+6 more)
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> apply_update : supported mutable drift for\nadmin_password,\nare_primary_whitelisted_ips_used,\nauto_refresh_frequency_in_seconds\n(+108 more)
apply_update --> sync_secret : update path completes
evaluate_ready --> sync_secret : apply secret policy\nready-only writes after\nACTIVE plus secret-input\nreads
sync_secret --> secret_blocked : Secret sync fails
secret_blocked --> sync_secret : retry Secret sync
sync_secret --> ready : Secret side effects succeed
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
ready --> delete_pending : delete requested
retryable --> delete_pending : delete requested
failed --> delete_pending : delete requested
delete_pending --> delete_cleanup_blocked : cleanup or finalizer release remains blocked
delete_cleanup_blocked --> deleted : retry delete completion until allowed
deleted --> deleted : terminal stutter
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Legacy-adapter controllers map
provider states into the shared controller
phases while open gaps keep additional
transitions explicit.
service: database
slug: autonomousdatabases
kind: AutonomousDatabases
archetype: legacy-adapter
status/finalizer: manual / none
requeue: provisioning, updating
provider states: create PROVISIONING, STARTING;
update MAINTENANCE_IN_PROGRESS, PROVISIONING,
RESTARTING, SCALE_IN_PROGRESS (+5 more); delete
TERMINATING, UNAVAILABLE
supported drift: admin_password,
are_primary_whitelisted_ips_used,
auto_refresh_frequency_in_seconds,
auto_refresh_point_lag_in_seconds (+107 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
autonomous_container_database_id,
autonomous_database_backup_id,
autonomous_database_id, character_set (+12 more)
and conflicts is_shrink_only ->
shrink_adb_trigger
list lookup: oci_database_autonomous_databases
filters autonomous_container_database_id,
compartment_id, db_version, db_workload (+9
more)
conflicts: is_shrink_only -> shrink_adb_trigger
open gaps: bind-versus-create,
delete-confirmation, legacy-adapter,
list-lookup, manual-webhook (+4 more)
Create first lists by displayName and
compartment before deciding to bind or create.
Wallet secret generation is optional and only
runs after the database is active.
Delete remains an unsupported legacy path, so no
terminating state is confirmed today.
end note
note right of delete_pending
delete policy: not-supported
delete observe: GetAutonomousDatabase or
ListAutonomousDatabases
delete targets: TERMINATED
Secret cleanup waits for OCI delete
confirmation.
end note
